1
00:00:14,067 --> 00:00:15,400
We are gathered together

2
00:00:15,533 --> 00:00:18,467
to bring together
on this momentous occasion

3
00:00:18,600 --> 00:00:19,700
to witness and to celebrate

4
00:00:19,833 --> 00:00:23,067
the wedding of Robert Rodriguez
and Elizabeth Morales.

5
00:00:24,100 --> 00:00:27,033
This wedding ceremony is a
public and legal affirmation,

6
00:00:27,167 --> 00:00:29,367
not abandoned,
and along with you,

7
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:31,867
the dearest and family
and friends

8
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:35,967
of Robert Rodriguez
and Elizabeth Morales...

9
00:00:37,033 --> 00:00:41,767
it's my honor and privilege
to officiate this significant

10
00:00:41,900 --> 00:00:44,700
and memorable event
of their lives.

11
00:00:44,833 --> 00:00:48,167
Is there anyone here who
objects to the marriage

12
00:00:48,300 --> 00:00:51,167
of Robert Rodriguez
and Elizabeth Morales.

13
00:00:51,300 --> 00:00:52,267
Ma'am, you're not allowed

14
00:00:52,400 --> 00:00:53,500
- to go inside.
- I don't care!

15
00:00:53,633 --> 00:00:54,567
I need to go inside!

16
00:00:54,700 --> 00:00:57,167
I now pronounce you
husband and wife.

17
00:00:57,300 --> 00:00:58,967
- Betsy!
- Sir, I'm sorry.

18
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:00,733
- Ma'am, you can't go in.
- Betsy, come here. Let's talk!

19
00:01:00,867 --> 00:01:03,133
Don't be a scene-stealer here.

20
00:01:03,267 --> 00:01:06,400
Try to ruin the wedding
party of your Daddy

21
00:01:06,533 --> 00:01:08,600
and I'll ruin your face.

22
00:01:08,767 --> 00:01:10,000
I'm his daughter!

23
00:01:10,133 --> 00:01:12,533
You're just his daughter.
I am the wife!

24
00:01:12,667 --> 00:01:16,200
We both know that you did
this to seek revenge on me.

25
00:01:16,333 --> 00:01:17,733
You're a user!

26
00:01:17,867 --> 00:01:19,200
And you...

27
00:01:19,333 --> 00:01:21,167
You're a thief!

28
00:01:21,300 --> 00:01:21,900
Betsy!

29
00:01:23,733 --> 00:01:25,767
Love, stop it!

30
00:01:25,900 --> 00:01:28,533
I regret that
I was generous to you.

31
00:01:28,667 --> 00:01:32,033
I regret ever calling you
my best friend!

32
00:01:32,167 --> 00:01:33,767
There's nothing you can do

33
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:35,867
because your Dad and I
are already married.

34
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:40,733
I am now your father's wife!

35
00:02:29,633 --> 00:02:31,267
<i> Dear Dad and Mom.</i>

36
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:34,200
<i>When you left me
to go to the US,</i>

37
00:02:34,333 --> 00:02:39,533
<i>I was so sad until I met Betsy.</i>

38
00:02:39,667 --> 00:02:41,700
<i>She's the daughter
of Nanny Susan.</i>

39
00:02:41,833 --> 00:02:44,967
<i> She's so nice and very funny.</i>

40
00:02:45,100 --> 00:02:49,000
<i>I'm happy that you met
a very good friend.</i>

41
00:02:49,167 --> 00:02:51,567
<i>Your Mommy and I
are working so hard</i>

42
00:02:51,700 --> 00:02:54,367
<i>to make sure
you'll have a good future.</i>

43
00:02:55,667 --> 00:02:57,900
<i> We miss you so much.</i>

44
00:02:58,033 --> 00:02:59,933
<i> Can't wait to see you.</i>

45
00:03:00,067 --> 00:03:03,100
<i> Love you, Dad and Mom.</i>

46
00:03:04,167 --> 00:03:06,600
<i>I miss you so much too,
Dad and Mom.</i>

47
00:03:06,733 --> 00:03:10,200
<i>Good thing Betsy is here
to cheer me up.</i>

48
00:03:10,333 --> 00:03:14,233
<i> You are the half of my wing.</i>

49
00:03:14,367 --> 00:03:18,767
<i>I want
to be your friend forever.</i>

50
00:03:18,900 --> 00:03:23,567
<i>She's my best friend and
she promised to be my FF.</i>

51
00:03:23,733 --> 00:03:25,833
<i> FF?</i>

52
00:03:25,967 --> 00:03:26,600
<i> What's that?</i>

53
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:31,933
<i>Forever Friend, Daddy.
You're so silly.</i>

54
00:03:34,033 --> 00:03:38,300
We will go to the mall later,
okay?

55
00:03:38,433 --> 00:03:42,333
KK but be careful.

56
00:03:42,467 --> 00:03:46,833
<i>I don't want anything
to happen to my baby.</i>

57
00:03:48,867 --> 00:03:52,833
I'm no longer a baby.

58
00:03:52,967 --> 00:03:53,767
Okay...

59
00:03:54,933 --> 00:03:57,200
take care.

60
00:03:57,333 --> 00:03:59,033
I miss you.

61
00:04:00,700 --> 00:04:02,333
Me too, Dad.

62
00:04:02,467 --> 00:04:04,000
Bye, for now, Dad.

63
00:04:04,133 --> 00:04:06,733
Betsy is waiting for me.

64
00:04:06,867 --> 00:04:09,400
Don't forget my request, okay?

65
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:11,600
K.K.

66
00:04:18,033 --> 00:04:19,933
Your balikbayan box is ready.

67
00:04:21,333 --> 00:04:23,400
Oh my gosh, thank you,
thank you, thank you,

68
00:04:23,533 --> 00:04:25,867
thank you, thank you!

69
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:29,133
I love you! I love you, I love
you and I miss you so much.

70
00:04:29,300 --> 00:04:32,033
I miss you, I miss you,
I love you.

71
00:04:34,667 --> 00:04:36,633
I love you too and I miss you.

72
00:04:36,767 --> 00:04:39,567
I love you. I love you so much.

73
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:44,367
You're the best my FF!

74
00:04:44,500 --> 00:04:46,767
My wing and forever friend.

75
00:04:46,900 --> 00:04:48,033
Are you happy?

76
00:04:48,167 --> 00:04:49,567
Of course!

77
00:04:55,300 --> 00:04:57,933
My new supplies are amazing!

78
00:05:06,867 --> 00:05:08,800
It smells so good.

79
00:05:08,933 --> 00:05:11,367
It's really different
if it's from the US, right?

80
00:05:15,067 --> 00:05:16,767
It's so beautiful.

81
00:05:21,233 --> 00:05:23,867
Your shoes are so beautiful.

82
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:27,767
They're all so pretty, right
they sent them for my birthday

83
00:05:27,900 --> 00:05:30,533
to match with dresses
they've ordered.

84
00:05:30,667 --> 00:05:34,733
It's so fuzzy for sweet sixteen.

85
00:05:34,900 --> 00:05:37,167
Can you wear all these?

86
00:05:37,300 --> 00:05:39,133
How many feet do you have?

87
00:05:39,267 --> 00:05:42,667
I think I've had four legs
for a long time now.

88
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:45,067
Two for me and two for you.

89
00:05:45,200 --> 00:05:46,133
There...

90
00:05:47,300 --> 00:05:49,633
now I have something
to wear on your birthday.

91
00:05:49,767 --> 00:05:51,167
Thank you, FF.

92
00:05:51,300 --> 00:05:53,433
Next time ask them
to buy you the latest bag

93
00:05:53,567 --> 00:05:55,167
and let me borrow it.

94
00:05:56,100 --> 00:05:57,467
Oh, by the way,

95
00:05:57,600 --> 00:05:59,933
I'll give you a pair of shoes.

96
00:06:00,067 --> 00:06:02,867
It's not here.

97
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:04,400
I'll just get it outside.

98
00:06:04,533 --> 00:06:05,367
- Okay.
- Just stay here.

99
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:06,667
Stay here.

100
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:07,633
Okay.

101
00:06:16,067 --> 00:06:17,300
It's so beautiful!

102
00:06:17,433 --> 00:06:21,833
Snacks for...

103
00:06:21,967 --> 00:06:25,233
Hey, hey, this kid...

104
00:06:25,367 --> 00:06:27,733
What did you hoard this time?

105
00:06:27,867 --> 00:06:29,233
You're so good.

106
00:06:29,367 --> 00:06:34,633
You know, you're worse than
a burglar, do you know that?

107
00:06:34,767 --> 00:06:37,100
You make it a point to get
things when I'm not around

108
00:06:37,233 --> 00:06:41,500
and then I will find out
that you took all her things.

109
00:06:41,667 --> 00:06:43,933
I didn't steal this from Gina.

110
00:06:44,067 --> 00:06:45,733
She gave these to me.

111
00:06:45,867 --> 00:06:48,867
That's because
you're fooling her.

112
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:49,633
Give me that.

113
00:06:49,767 --> 00:06:51,533
- Give me that!
- Wait a second.

114
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:55,767
You broke it.

115
00:06:55,900 --> 00:06:56,733
Me?

116
00:06:56,867 --> 00:06:58,367
Auntie...

117
00:06:58,500 --> 00:07:00,900
don't take that from Betsy.

118
00:07:01,033 --> 00:07:02,533
That's hers already.

119
00:07:04,200 --> 00:07:06,033
Hey kid,

120
00:07:06,167 --> 00:07:08,800
you're taking advantage.

121
00:07:08,933 --> 00:07:11,967
The truth is, you shouldn't be
allowed to set foot here

122
00:07:12,100 --> 00:07:15,300
because I fired
your mother a long time ago!

123
00:07:15,467 --> 00:07:18,200
All you do
is make cash advances.

124
00:07:18,333 --> 00:07:19,500
You guys are abusive.

125
00:07:19,633 --> 00:07:21,167
Don't ever come back here
to our house,

126
00:07:21,300 --> 00:07:22,033
do you understand?

127
00:07:22,167 --> 00:07:23,767
Don't come back here!

128
00:07:23,900 --> 00:07:25,300
Auntie,

129
00:07:25,433 --> 00:07:28,533
don't accuse Betsy like that.

130
00:07:28,667 --> 00:07:30,067
She's my friend

131
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:34,033
and I won't allow you
to stop her from coming here.

132
00:07:38,767 --> 00:07:40,433
You're so stupid!

133
00:07:40,567 --> 00:07:43,767
Why did you let that
witch Connie catch you?

134
00:07:43,900 --> 00:07:45,733
Do you know that perfume?

135
00:07:45,867 --> 00:07:48,967
You can sell that
for more than five hundred!

136
00:07:49,133 --> 00:07:51,600
Mother, what's with you?

137
00:07:51,733 --> 00:07:54,167
Where's the red dress?

138
00:07:54,300 --> 00:07:57,567
That's all I have left
of everything I got from Gina!

139
00:07:59,967 --> 00:08:01,367
Don't look for it anymore!

140
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:03,767
Just get something
on the next package.

141
00:08:03,900 --> 00:08:06,433
But Mother,
there won't be a next time!

142
00:08:07,867 --> 00:08:09,833
I'm having a hard time
getting through Ma'am Connie.

143
00:08:10,867 --> 00:08:12,267
Auntie Connie.

144
00:08:13,467 --> 00:08:14,467
Sorry.

145
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:20,600
You know, Gina,

146
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:23,467
I was really shocked

147
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:26,200
when you answered me back
just because of Betsy.

148
00:08:27,133 --> 00:08:29,233
I'm really sorry...

149
00:08:29,367 --> 00:08:32,400
but I was just defending
my friend.

150
00:08:34,100 --> 00:08:35,600
How about me?

151
00:08:35,733 --> 00:08:37,133
Who am I to you?

152
00:08:39,100 --> 00:08:43,333
I'm the only one who took care
of you since your parents left.

153
00:08:43,467 --> 00:08:45,700
Gina, you're like a daughter
to me

154
00:08:45,833 --> 00:08:48,167
that's why
I'm only concerned about you.

155
00:08:49,433 --> 00:08:53,500
Haven't I been reminding you
for a long time?

156
00:08:53,633 --> 00:08:57,233
That Betsy is like a leech.

157
00:08:58,233 --> 00:09:01,733
She likes getting close to you
so she can get things from you.

158
00:09:01,867 --> 00:09:03,233
Auntie...

159
00:09:03,367 --> 00:09:05,600
it's unfair for you
to judge her.

160
00:09:06,633 --> 00:09:08,633
Did you sell the dress?

161
00:09:08,767 --> 00:09:09,600
Yes!

162
00:09:10,533 --> 00:09:11,600
To pay for our debts.

163
00:09:11,733 --> 00:09:16,233
But Mother, I really wanted that
that's why I hid it!

164
00:09:16,367 --> 00:09:18,500
I'm the one who's getting
Gina's things,

165
00:09:18,633 --> 00:09:20,667
I'm the one selling them
and then what?

166
00:09:20,800 --> 00:09:22,967
Nothing goes to me!

167
00:09:23,100 --> 00:09:24,033
Why?

168
00:09:24,167 --> 00:09:26,300
Are my observations wrong?

169
00:09:26,433 --> 00:09:28,667
Didn't she always
ask things from you

170
00:09:28,833 --> 00:09:30,400
and you always give her?

171
00:09:30,533 --> 00:09:32,767
That's how friends are, right?

172
00:09:32,900 --> 00:09:34,067
Give and take.

173
00:09:35,467 --> 00:09:37,400
Gina, all she does is take!

174
00:09:41,933 --> 00:09:46,067
Okay, it's not bad to share

175
00:09:46,200 --> 00:09:49,733
but there are limits, Gina.

176
00:09:49,867 --> 00:09:52,467
Maybe one day,
you'll wake up,

177
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:54,367
you're the one
who doesn't have anything

178
00:09:54,500 --> 00:09:56,500
because you've already given
everything to her.

179
00:09:56,633 --> 00:09:57,867
How about her?

180
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:59,900
What does she give you?

181
00:10:00,033 --> 00:10:02,000
- Nothing, right?
- There is, Auntie.

182
00:10:03,167 --> 00:10:06,200
It's like I'm not sending you
to school and feeding you!

183
00:10:06,333 --> 00:10:08,800
But you're benefiting from me.

184
00:10:08,933 --> 00:10:11,800
My education in the public
school, that's free!

185
00:10:11,933 --> 00:10:14,767
Even my allowance
is still my responsibility!

186
00:10:16,033 --> 00:10:19,433
From the time Mommy and Daddy
left until now,

187
00:10:19,567 --> 00:10:21,333
she's always been with me.

188
00:10:21,467 --> 00:10:24,333
I struggled so much
and I was sad.

189
00:10:24,467 --> 00:10:26,933
But Betsy
was always there for me.

190
00:10:27,067 --> 00:10:29,933
I know that she's asking
for a lot.

191
00:10:30,067 --> 00:10:31,700
But at least,

192
00:10:31,833 --> 00:10:33,200
she's always there.

193
00:10:34,233 --> 00:10:35,800
She never left me.

194
00:10:43,167 --> 00:10:44,933
What's that?

195
00:10:45,067 --> 00:10:48,767
You two, your mouths
reach the other barangay.

196
00:10:51,467 --> 00:10:52,400
Susan, what's for dinner?

197
00:10:52,533 --> 00:10:55,233
Nothing yet,
I'm just about to cook.

198
00:10:55,367 --> 00:10:56,633
That's what I like about you.

199
00:10:58,533 --> 00:10:59,667
Hey, hey, hey!

200
00:10:59,800 --> 00:11:01,033
Where are you going?

201
00:11:01,167 --> 00:11:04,067
Back to your childhood friend
who's head over heels over you

202
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:07,700
but starving like us?

203
00:11:07,867 --> 00:11:12,667
He's not lazy and just
drinking like your men!

204
00:11:12,800 --> 00:11:14,567
I can count on Gerald!

205
00:11:16,900 --> 00:11:19,033
Your daughter's mouth is filthy.

206
00:11:38,400 --> 00:11:41,700
Where exactly is the new place
Betsy moved to?

207
00:12:15,700 --> 00:12:17,033
Stay in front of me.

208
00:12:27,400 --> 00:12:28,200
Here.

209
00:12:28,333 --> 00:12:29,167
Are you okay?

210
00:12:29,300 --> 00:12:30,767
Did you get hurt?

211
00:12:30,900 --> 00:12:32,167
No, not at all.

212
00:12:32,300 --> 00:12:33,267
Thank you.

213
00:12:33,400 --> 00:12:34,433
That's nothing.

214
00:12:35,700 --> 00:12:37,533
Here, use this first.

215
00:12:38,667 --> 00:12:40,900
Put this on and endure it.

216
00:12:41,033 --> 00:12:42,833
You might get hurt.

217
00:12:48,567 --> 00:12:49,633
But what about you?

218
00:12:49,767 --> 00:12:52,733
It's okay.
Our house is just near here.

219
00:12:53,800 --> 00:12:55,467
What's your name?

220
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:56,567
Gina.

221
00:12:56,700 --> 00:12:57,633
And I'm...

222
00:12:57,767 --> 00:12:58,600
Gerald?

223
00:13:00,100 --> 00:13:01,400
Hey!

224
00:13:02,633 --> 00:13:05,167
Gerald is flirting
with someone else.

225
00:13:05,300 --> 00:13:07,433
She's prettier than Betsy.

226
00:13:07,567 --> 00:13:08,600
You're crazy!

227
00:13:08,733 --> 00:13:12,933
Gina is my FF and we're
just as pretty, aren't we?

228
00:13:13,067 --> 00:13:14,800
But why are you
and Gerald together?

229
00:13:14,933 --> 00:13:16,233
What are you doing here?

230
00:13:16,367 --> 00:13:19,600
You know I was going to your
place so I can give this to you.

231
00:13:21,700 --> 00:13:24,067
The dog even chased me.

232
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:25,400
Good thing

233
00:13:26,667 --> 00:13:28,433
he's there to save me.

234
00:13:28,567 --> 00:13:30,100
Gerald's really kind.

235
00:13:30,233 --> 00:13:32,233
He's hardworking
and always reliable.

236
00:13:32,367 --> 00:13:33,167
And handsome?

237
00:13:34,633 --> 00:13:36,100
Where's the handsome guy?

238
00:13:36,233 --> 00:13:37,600
Where?

239
00:13:44,500 --> 00:13:45,967
Which one of these will
you wear on your birthday?

240
00:13:49,167 --> 00:13:52,500
Have you and Gerald known
each other for a long time?

241
00:13:52,633 --> 00:13:56,633
Yes, we're childhood friends
and we're neighbors.

242
00:13:56,800 --> 00:13:58,900
Why didn't you tell me
about him?

243
00:13:59,933 --> 00:14:02,500
I think I mentioned him
to you before.

244
00:14:02,633 --> 00:14:04,367
You probably
just didn't remember.

245
00:14:04,500 --> 00:14:05,667
But are you close?

246
00:14:06,600 --> 00:14:07,967
Yes, very much.

247
00:14:12,800 --> 00:14:13,667
Wait.

248
00:14:15,733 --> 00:14:18,833
You asked me a lot of questions
about Gerald?

249
00:14:18,967 --> 00:14:20,500
Is he your type?

250
00:14:20,633 --> 00:14:22,400
That's you.

251
00:14:22,533 --> 00:14:24,533
You said you were close.

252
00:14:24,667 --> 00:14:26,633
Maybe you're the one
who likes him?

253
00:14:26,767 --> 00:14:28,467
Oh, no!

254
00:14:28,633 --> 00:14:30,200
He's just my friend!

255
00:14:30,333 --> 00:14:33,433
Is it okay if I invite him
to my birthday?

256
00:14:33,567 --> 00:14:34,500
Sure.

257
00:14:34,633 --> 00:14:35,933
We'll attend together.

258
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:40,067
But, FF,

259
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:42,567
I don't have anything
to wear yet.

260
00:14:42,700 --> 00:14:44,233
There are two of them.

261
00:14:47,633 --> 00:14:49,433
Can I have one?

262
00:14:50,400 --> 00:14:51,867
Sure,

263
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:53,767
you can borrow anything.

264
00:14:55,300 --> 00:14:56,700
Do you know why?

265
00:14:57,833 --> 00:15:01,400
I'm going to wear something
and it's perfect!

266
00:15:09,067 --> 00:15:10,567
Which suits me better?

267
00:15:16,200 --> 00:15:17,767
It's beautiful!

268
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:25,233
This is what I chose because
this dress is so special!

269
00:15:33,800 --> 00:15:34,500
Wait a minute.

270
00:15:34,667 --> 00:15:36,300
I'll just talk to them, Daddy.

271
00:15:36,433 --> 00:15:37,233
Okay.

272
00:16:00,767 --> 00:16:03,300
Are you going to wear the dress
that I gave to your mom?

273
00:16:03,433 --> 00:16:06,667
Yes, because I was inspired
by your stories

274
00:16:06,800 --> 00:16:09,667
that Mommy used that dress
at your prom.

275
00:16:09,833 --> 00:16:12,433
She said she's going to wear
the dress I gave you.

276
00:16:12,567 --> 00:16:13,733
Did you know at first,

277
00:16:13,867 --> 00:16:16,900
I wasn't confident
wearing that dress?

278
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:22,033
But, your dad told me
that I look pretty in it.

279
00:16:22,167 --> 00:16:23,433
He said I'm cute.

280
00:16:23,567 --> 00:16:28,067
And I'm sure, you're going to
look just as good as your mom.

281
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:31,300
The important thing is that
you're happy on your birthday.

282
00:16:31,433 --> 00:16:33,600
All we wish
is for your happiness.

283
00:16:33,733 --> 00:16:37,233
We wish that nobody destroys

284
00:16:37,367 --> 00:16:41,267
or takes away
that happiness from you. Okay?

285
00:16:46,933 --> 00:16:48,433
It's beautiful.

286
00:16:48,567 --> 00:16:50,000
It looks perfect on me.

287
00:16:51,800 --> 00:16:52,700
Betsy!

288
00:16:55,900 --> 00:16:56,900
Why did you wear that?

289
00:16:57,567 --> 00:17:00,333
Didn't I say, that's what
I'll wear on my birthday?

290
00:17:00,467 --> 00:17:02,300
Is this really what you chose?

291
00:17:02,433 --> 00:17:04,667
It looks old.

292
00:17:04,800 --> 00:17:06,700
You can donate it to me.

293
00:17:06,833 --> 00:17:08,067
Betsy, no!

294
00:17:08,200 --> 00:17:10,667
I've been lending you
my other dress,

295
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:12,667
but not this one!

296
00:17:12,800 --> 00:17:14,100
Is that it?

297
00:17:14,233 --> 00:17:16,900
Are you already nagging me
about the things you gave me?

298
00:17:17,067 --> 00:17:18,700
No, Betsy!

299
00:17:18,833 --> 00:17:21,000
I'm willing to share
everything with you,

300
00:17:21,133 --> 00:17:25,367
but I already told you,
this dress belongs to my mom!

301
00:17:25,500 --> 00:17:27,167
I'm not stealing it, okay?

302
00:17:27,300 --> 00:17:28,800
I was just trying it on!

303
00:17:28,933 --> 00:17:30,467
- It's a bit tight...
- Betsy, what's with you?

304
00:17:30,600 --> 00:17:31,800
- Wait a minute.
- My Mom gave that to me.

305
00:17:31,933 --> 00:17:33,767
- Wait, don't yell at me!
- Take it off!

306
00:17:33,900 --> 00:17:34,567
Okay, here. Here it is.

307
00:17:34,700 --> 00:17:35,400
Here! You can have that!

308
00:17:35,533 --> 00:17:36,433
You can have it!

309
00:17:38,133 --> 00:17:39,867
There you go!

310
00:17:49,300 --> 00:17:50,000
There you go.

311
00:17:56,033 --> 00:17:58,800
This dress has sentimental
value to Mommy and Daddy.

312
00:17:58,933 --> 00:18:00,400
And then you just ruined it?

313
00:18:00,533 --> 00:18:01,833
Well, it's your fault!

314
00:18:01,967 --> 00:18:03,333
You're pulling it!

315
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:07,400
I thought I could wear it!

316
00:18:07,533 --> 00:18:09,200
And then you're
suddenly snatching it away?

317
00:18:09,333 --> 00:18:11,900
Why are you making it look
like I'm snatching it away

318
00:18:12,033 --> 00:18:13,200
when this is mine?

319
00:18:13,333 --> 00:18:14,367
You are over the top!

320
00:18:14,500 --> 00:18:17,100
You only want it because
it's your mommy's, right?

321
00:18:17,233 --> 00:18:18,433
Why?

322
00:18:18,567 --> 00:18:22,167
If you wear it, will you forget
that your parents left you?

323
00:18:22,333 --> 00:18:24,600
That is so mean!

324
00:18:24,733 --> 00:18:26,533
It's true!

325
00:18:26,667 --> 00:18:29,233
No one else is patient
with you but me!

326
00:18:30,500 --> 00:18:31,267
Oh, there you go!

327
00:18:31,400 --> 00:18:32,867
Just be friends with that!

328
00:18:38,433 --> 00:18:39,533
Wait.

329
00:18:39,667 --> 00:18:40,567
Are you leaving?

330
00:18:40,700 --> 00:18:42,200
Yes!

331
00:18:42,333 --> 00:18:44,933
Maybe you'll have something
to blame me for.

332
00:18:45,067 --> 00:18:49,500
Sorry because I'm poor so I'm
counting on your donations!

333
00:18:49,633 --> 00:18:51,800
But remember,

334
00:18:51,933 --> 00:18:53,833
even if you have
a lot of nice things

335
00:18:53,967 --> 00:18:55,400
and other friends...

336
00:18:56,500 --> 00:18:59,300
you won't find
a best friend like me!

337
00:18:59,433 --> 00:19:00,967
I know that.

338
00:19:01,900 --> 00:19:03,467
You should be grateful

339
00:19:04,467 --> 00:19:06,067
because even though your aunt
is annoyed with me,

340
00:19:06,200 --> 00:19:08,267
I'm still here with you!

341
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:10,767
But if you don't want me
to be your friend anymore

342
00:19:10,900 --> 00:19:12,833
Then I won't show myself
to you anymore.

343
00:19:13,833 --> 00:19:15,267
Don't, Betsy.

344
00:19:16,333 --> 00:19:17,767
Sorry if you
just misinterpreted me.

345
00:19:17,900 --> 00:19:19,633
I was just really surprised.

346
00:19:20,667 --> 00:19:22,967
It's easy to repair
a ruined dress.

347
00:19:24,033 --> 00:19:26,267
But when our friendship
is broken,

348
00:19:26,400 --> 00:19:27,767
it's hard to get it back.

349
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:30,633
You're the one to blame
if that happens!

350
00:19:32,433 --> 00:19:34,900
Because you said you'd be
generous to me, remember?

351
00:19:36,400 --> 00:19:41,900
And now, just for this dress
are you going to fight me?

352
00:19:42,033 --> 00:19:44,033
That's why I'm really sorry,
Betsy.

353
00:19:45,067 --> 00:19:48,500
I didn't mean
to offend or hurt you,

354
00:19:48,633 --> 00:19:51,033
and I know
you're the same way with me.

355
00:19:51,167 --> 00:19:53,400
You've always been loyal to me.

356
00:19:54,533 --> 00:19:55,567
That's the thing

357
00:19:56,667 --> 00:19:59,200
I'm always by your side
when you need me,

358
00:20:00,233 --> 00:20:02,433
and I hope you remember that.

359
00:20:04,067 --> 00:20:06,467
At least,
I'm keeping my promise to you.

360
00:20:07,100 --> 00:20:08,633
I know,

361
00:20:08,767 --> 00:20:13,267
and I appreciate
everything you do for me.

362
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:16,200
I am so thankful...

363
00:20:16,333 --> 00:20:18,267
that you are my best friend.

364
00:20:18,400 --> 00:20:20,900
I still want to share
all this with you.

365
00:20:21,033 --> 00:20:23,433
I will still keep my promise

366
00:20:23,567 --> 00:20:26,567
that I will be a good friend
because I love you,

367
00:20:26,700 --> 00:20:27,700
I swear!

368
00:20:28,500 --> 00:20:30,400
I don't want to lose you, Betsy.

369
00:20:30,533 --> 00:20:31,567
Really?

370
00:20:32,433 --> 00:20:33,467
You're the one who's going
to leave for the US

371
00:20:33,600 --> 00:20:36,467
and leave me behind.

372
00:20:36,633 --> 00:20:40,167
Maybe when you're in America
you'll forget about me!

373
00:20:41,367 --> 00:20:42,000
No.

374
00:20:43,100 --> 00:20:45,300
That will never happen.

375
00:20:45,433 --> 00:20:50,267
You can fly to the US
so we can always be together.

376
00:20:50,400 --> 00:20:52,867
So I hope
we're still friends forever?

377
00:20:54,567 --> 00:20:57,400
I know you can't survive
without me.

378
00:21:10,900 --> 00:21:12,400
- Hurry up, hurry up!
- Oh my Betsy!

379
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:15,067
Oh my,
your friend is just so kind.

380
00:21:15,200 --> 00:21:17,200
If I were Gina
and you ruined my gown?

381
00:21:17,333 --> 00:21:19,033
Oh my, you're a dead child.

382
00:21:19,167 --> 00:21:23,467
Mother, she already said sorry.
Besides, Betsy is kind.

383
00:21:23,600 --> 00:21:25,167
There's nothing we can do.

384
00:21:25,300 --> 00:21:31,333
- Gerald is in love!
- Hey, stop it, you guys!

385
00:21:31,467 --> 00:21:34,067
And, Gerald, hurry up
and follow me outside.

386
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:34,867
Yes, Mother.

387
00:21:36,967 --> 00:21:38,967
Excuse me, let me pass.

388
00:21:39,100 --> 00:21:40,500
Thank you.

389
00:21:40,633 --> 00:21:42,133
Thank you!

390
00:21:45,433 --> 00:21:48,800
You don't have anything to wear
for Gina's birthday?

391
00:21:48,933 --> 00:21:50,200
Yes, I have nothing to wear.

392
00:21:50,333 --> 00:21:51,433
I was embarrassed to borrow

393
00:21:51,567 --> 00:21:54,200
because I ruined
her mother's dress.

394
00:21:56,233 --> 00:21:58,233
This is about five hundred.

395
00:21:58,367 --> 00:22:00,633
This is enough to buy
a dress at the thrift store.

396
00:22:00,767 --> 00:22:02,267
Come, I'll go with you now.

397
00:22:03,333 --> 00:22:06,167
You're going to spend your
savings to buy me a dress?

398
00:22:06,300 --> 00:22:07,200
Yes.

399
00:22:10,267 --> 00:22:12,467
Awesome! How sweet!

400
00:22:12,600 --> 00:22:14,600
- Is that true?
- Yes.

401
00:22:14,733 --> 00:22:17,933
Seriously, and that's not all...

402
00:22:20,400 --> 00:22:24,667
Tell her so you'll know!

403
00:22:24,800 --> 00:22:28,600
And if it's hopeless move on!

404
00:22:28,733 --> 00:22:29,733
Right!

405
00:22:33,167 --> 00:22:34,433
You guys are such a jerk!

406
00:22:35,133 --> 00:22:36,233
Whatever, guys.

407
00:22:38,100 --> 00:22:38,967
Oh no.

408
00:22:40,500 --> 00:22:41,633
These two are something else.

409
00:22:41,767 --> 00:22:42,800
It's your fault!

410
00:22:42,933 --> 00:22:44,600
You don't know your limits.

411
00:22:44,733 --> 00:22:46,267
Betsy!

412
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:47,867
Betsy, wait a minute!

413
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:48,767
Betsy.

414
00:22:51,033 --> 00:22:53,267
Don't buy me clothes!

415
00:22:53,400 --> 00:22:57,033
I want to and
that's not all I want for you,

416
00:22:57,167 --> 00:22:58,100
because...

417
00:23:00,133 --> 00:23:00,833
I like you.

418
00:23:01,967 --> 00:23:04,067
I have liked you
ever since we were just kids.

419
00:23:05,833 --> 00:23:07,733
You're full of drama!

420
00:23:07,867 --> 00:23:10,100
What's with you? Just relax!

421
00:23:10,233 --> 00:23:11,467
I like you too, Gerald.

422
00:23:11,600 --> 00:23:13,133
We're part
of the same friend group.

423
00:23:13,267 --> 00:23:15,867
We're friends, that's it!

424
00:23:27,500 --> 00:23:30,433
Oh, Betsy herself said
that you're just friends.

425
00:23:30,567 --> 00:23:32,100
She won't fall in love with you.

426
00:23:32,233 --> 00:23:33,433
But why is it like that?

427
00:23:33,567 --> 00:23:35,067
She's so affectionate with me.

428
00:23:35,200 --> 00:23:37,700
I appreciate what she's doing.

429
00:23:37,833 --> 00:23:39,000
Maybe Betsy is used
to being like that to you

430
00:23:39,133 --> 00:23:40,800
because you're so close.

431
00:23:40,933 --> 00:23:41,933
But you're the only one hoping

432
00:23:42,067 --> 00:23:43,700
that you can be
more than friends.

433
00:23:46,733 --> 00:23:47,833
Gerald!

434
00:23:47,967 --> 00:23:49,367
Have you seen Betsy?

435
00:23:49,500 --> 00:23:51,767
She has a practice
with her groupmates.

436
00:23:52,833 --> 00:23:54,000
By the way.

437
00:23:54,133 --> 00:23:56,300
Are you busy this weekend?

438
00:23:56,467 --> 00:23:59,833
It's my birthday party,
you and Mackie are invited.

439
00:23:59,967 --> 00:24:01,733
Oh, yes! I'm game with that!

440
00:24:01,867 --> 00:24:02,800
Formal wear, right?

441
00:24:02,933 --> 00:24:04,600
- Yes.
- Okay, okay.

442
00:24:04,733 --> 00:24:08,367
This is the dress that Betsy is
going to wear for my birthday.

443
00:24:08,500 --> 00:24:10,267
She forgot
to bring it last time.

444
00:24:10,400 --> 00:24:12,200
Can you just give it to her?

445
00:24:12,333 --> 00:24:13,433
Thank you.

446
00:24:13,567 --> 00:24:15,467
Betsy won't have any problem
with what to wear anymore.

447
00:24:15,600 --> 00:24:16,567
Thank you.

448
00:24:32,867 --> 00:24:34,800
Yes, by the way,

449
00:24:34,933 --> 00:24:36,767
can I ask you a favor?

450
00:24:39,600 --> 00:24:43,333
Is it okay
if you will be my escort?

451
00:24:43,467 --> 00:24:45,033
What? Me?

452
00:24:45,933 --> 00:24:48,167
I mean, if it's okay.

453
00:24:48,300 --> 00:24:50,467
I mean, we're friends, right?

454
00:24:53,633 --> 00:24:55,233
Yes, okay.

455
00:24:55,367 --> 00:24:56,133
Really?

456
00:24:56,267 --> 00:24:57,133
Thank you!

457
00:25:06,400 --> 00:25:07,600
Sorry.

458
00:25:07,733 --> 00:25:09,667
I thought you wouldn't agree.

459
00:25:09,800 --> 00:25:11,167
Anyway...

460
00:25:11,300 --> 00:25:12,700
see you this weekend?

461
00:25:14,333 --> 00:25:16,200
- Bye, guys.
- Bye.

462
00:25:27,733 --> 00:25:28,967
Gina's cute, isn't she?

463
00:25:30,300 --> 00:25:31,867
You'll tease me again.

464
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:34,100
Why don't you just court her?

465
00:25:34,233 --> 00:25:36,233
It seems you stand a chance
compared to Betsy

466
00:25:36,400 --> 00:25:37,867
who doesn't like you!

467
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:39,067
Let's go.

468
00:25:50,100 --> 00:25:52,100
Hey! That's enough!

469
00:25:52,233 --> 00:25:54,067
It's Gina you came here for.

470
00:25:56,633 --> 00:26:00,967
<i>Welcome to Gina's sweet sixteen
birthday celebration!</i>

471
00:26:03,467 --> 00:26:08,100
<i>And now, let us all welcome our
lovely birthday celebrant,</i>

472
00:26:08,233 --> 00:26:12,433
<i> Ms. Gina Marie Rodriguez!</i>

473
00:26:37,800 --> 00:26:39,867
Thank you for choosing me
as your escort.

474
00:26:40,000 --> 00:26:42,267
I hope I can make
your whole night happy.

475
00:27:07,300 --> 00:27:10,767
Not everyone who says
she's your true friend

476
00:27:10,900 --> 00:27:12,600
is telling the truth.

477
00:27:12,733 --> 00:27:14,267
I don't want
to see you get hurt.

478
00:27:14,400 --> 00:27:16,733
I don't want you
to get fooled by anyone.

479
00:27:16,900 --> 00:27:18,667
- You made me look like a fool!
- Wow!

480
00:27:18,800 --> 00:27:19,633
Is that the one
who looks like a fool?

481
00:27:19,767 --> 00:27:20,967
I'm going to live
in the States soon!

482
00:27:21,100 --> 00:27:22,667
You know, Gina,
you're so arrogant!

483
00:27:22,800 --> 00:27:25,200
This isn't the life for me.

484
00:27:25,333 --> 00:27:27,800
I belong in the US,
with my parents.

485
00:27:27,933 --> 00:27:29,267
Gina, Gina! Let me explain!

486
00:27:29,400 --> 00:27:30,867
What are you going to explain
to me?

487
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:31,733
Mark?

488
00:27:31,867 --> 00:27:33,700
I need a break
from this breakup.

489
00:27:33,833 --> 00:27:34,833
Let go of me!

490
00:27:34,967 --> 00:27:36,367
Hey!

491
00:27:36,500 --> 00:27:37,700
Are you okay?

492
00:27:37,833 --> 00:27:38,733
Gina?

493
00:27:38,867 --> 00:27:40,000
Gerald?

494
00:27:40,133 --> 00:27:42,300
I'm so happy that you and
Gerald are still going strong.

495
00:27:42,433 --> 00:27:44,833
Imagine, who'd thought we'd be
together for a long time?

496
00:27:44,967 --> 00:27:47,400
Betsy, Morales, but your name
is still not there.

497
00:27:47,533 --> 00:27:48,900
This is my third take.

498
00:27:49,067 --> 00:27:51,700
No more! I'm done, Gerald!

499
00:27:51,833 --> 00:27:54,333
There are many other ways
for you to come to the US.

500
00:27:54,467 --> 00:27:58,667
It would be easier if one of us
marries a US citizen.

501
00:27:58,800 --> 00:28:00,367
Marry Gerald.

502
00:28:00,500 --> 00:28:01,367
What?

503
00:28:01,500 --> 00:28:02,900
So that's the plan
you're thinking about?

504
00:28:03,033 --> 00:28:04,367
That I'll marry Gina?

505
00:28:04,500 --> 00:28:05,600
Do you think I'll agree?

506
00:28:05,733 --> 00:28:07,567
I am going to flirt
with that American.

507
00:28:07,700 --> 00:28:10,167
He'll be Gerald and
my ticket to America!

508
00:28:10,300 --> 00:28:11,267
Don't be a smart aleck.

509
00:28:11,400 --> 00:28:13,333
After all, you don't want
to marry him, remember?

510
00:28:14,733 --> 00:28:15,633
Betsy!

511
00:28:15,767 --> 00:28:18,267
I want to at least
make up with her.

512
00:28:18,400 --> 00:28:20,667
Gina, you won't get
anything out of it.

513
00:28:20,800 --> 00:28:22,333
For Betsy's sake,

514
00:28:22,500 --> 00:28:23,967
marry me.
